Name: submucous uterine fibroid
Definition: An uterine fibroid that is located adjacent to the lining of the uterus.

Name: subserous uterine fibroid
Definition: An uterine fibroid that is located adjacent to the outside of the uterus.

Name: uterine corpus epithelioid leiomyoma
Definition: An uterine fibroid that is characterized by the presence of round epithelioid

Name: uterine corpus dissecting leiomyoma
Definition: A uterine fibroid that is characterized by the presence of intramural tearing.

Name: obsolete mitotically active variant uterine corpus leiomyoma
Definition: A uterine fibroid that is characterized by the presence of intramural tearing.

Name: uterus interstitial leiomyoma
Definition: An uterine fibroid that is located within the myometrium.

Name: uterine corpus myxoid leiomyoma
Definition: An uterine fibroid that is characterized by islands of smooth muscle in myxoid connective tissue that contain large vessels

Name: uterine corpus lipoleiomyoma
Definition: An uterine fibroid that is characterized by the presence of adipocytes.
